# Safe Response

A high fever that lasts for three days should not be ignored. While many fevers are caused by viral infections that improve on their own, a persistent or worsening fever may indicate a condition that requires medical evaluation.

Stay well hydrated, get adequate rest, and consider using fever-reducing medication if appropriate and according to the product instructions or advice from a healthcare professional.

You should seek prompt medical attention if your fever is very high, lasts several days, is accompanied by difficulty breathing, severe headache, confusion, persistent vomiting, rash, or other concerning symptoms.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

A response can become unsafe not only by providing incorrect information but also by discouraging appropriate medical care. Safety evaluations should consider the real-world consequences if a user follows the advice.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

For future evaluations, I would assess both the factual accuracy of medical claims and whether the advice encourages or discourages appropriate healthcare when warning signs are present.

